  "texts": [
    "2 https://erosita.mpe.mpg.de/dr1/eSASS4DR1/eSASS4DR1_ CALDB/ A34, page 3 of 38 Merloni, A., et al.",
    ": A&A, 682, A34 (2024) PSF calibrationGiven the scientific objectives of eROSITA, i.e.",
    "imaging the whole sky at soft-to-hard X-ray energies with good sensitivity to low surface brightness diffuse and extended emission, clusters of galaxies in particular, an accurate calibration of the telescopes' Point-Spread Function (PSF) is critical.",
    "As we describe in greater detail below (Sect. 4), the catalogues presented here have been constructed using a single photon mode, in which the PSF of each telescope module at the location of each detected event on the CCD is accounted for, using a shapelet-based model calibrated on the extensive dataset accumulated on ground before the launch (Dennerl et al.",
    "A description of the shapeletbased PSF modelling, and its usage in scanning mode can be found in Appendix B.1 of Brunner et al. (2022).While work is ongoing to accurately characterize eROSITA's PSF based on the survey data themselves, here we report on a preliminary analysis that confirms the reliability of the onground calibration adopted for the DR1 datasets."
  ]
}